  "text": "Unfortunately, there are also some pitfalls with Eulerian techniques. They are known to fail for large motions, and also require the user to manually specify frequencies of interest [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Furthermore, period-to-period drift due to a moving camera or small motion variations can be problematic, as can unrelated motion in the background or occlusions [CITATION_3] .",
